                            <comment id="14394983" author="srikanth235" created="Fri, 3 Apr 2015 19:44:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Are you okay with defaulting this to 10 seconds or do you think we should go for better defaulting?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
+    FSUtils.waitOnSafeMode(c, c.getInt(HConstants.MASTER_WAIT_ON_SAFE_MODE, 10 * 1000));
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14395042" author="esteban" created="Fri, 3 Apr 2015 20:40:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;10 seconds should be fine since operators and tools basically wait until HDFS is out of safemode in order to start HBase. This only adds the possibility to change tune it separately for those that would like to start HDï¿½FS and HBase at the same time.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
